This is indeed the Yak 38 &quot;Forger&quot;
The Soviet naval attaches made the original &quot;Yak 36&quot; statement - in the 1976 press release as &quot;Kiev&quot; passed through the Bosporus straight - but it was not until the early 80's that the mistake was cleared up in the Eastern bloc aviation press and it was correctly identified as the Yak 38 &quot;Forger&quot;

30 years later it seems silly to play such guessing games - yet we are going through it all again with the Chinese.
